Type switches are a special construct. Don't try to understand
them by comparing them to other types of switch-case.
The syntax is as follows:
switch v := i.(type) {
case bool:
    // v is of type bool
case int:
    // v is of type int
case *int:
    // v is of type *int
default:
    // v has the same type as i
}

var i interface{} = int(4)

x := i.(int) // panics if i is not of type int
y, ok := i.(float) // lets you check ok before using y

